The paper deals with the topological complexity of languages of Petri nets, which is a topic in logic and automata theory. The use of ordinals and the Borel and Wadge hierarchies suggests a connection to descriptive set theory, which is a subfield of mathematical logic. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial and formal language aspects, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), respectively. The use of Petri nets suggests a connection to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity), as Petri nets are often used in the study of concurrent and distributed systems, which are topics in these sub-categories.
